r social change in the asia pacific region including northeast southeast and south asia or topics in international relations and international political economy fellows must be in residence for the duration of the appointment which begins the fall quarter of the 2012 2013 academic year they must take part in center activities throughout the academic year and are required to present their research findings in center seminars fellows also participate in the center's publication program the fellowship includes a stipend of $50000 for 10 months plus $3000 for research materials applicants should submit brief research statement not to exceed five typed pages which describes the research and writing to be undertaken during the fellowship period as well as the proposed publishable product curriculum vitae and three letters of recommendation deadline for receipt of all materials is december 31 2011 submit all materials and queries to fellowship coordinator victoria kwong shorenstein aparc stanford university encina hall room e301 stanford ca 94305 6055 650 723 2408 voice 650 723 6530 fax vckwong stanford edu search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages fellowship news shorenstein postdoctoral fellowship program grows march 9 2012 news opportunity for two junior scholars studying contemporary asia september 2 2011 announcement kushida named takahashi research associate august 9 2011 japan studies program news conditions for equitable development in southeast asia june 13 2011 seaf news new fellows to study china's automotive industry and religious tolerance in indonesia march 18 2011 announcement hedging alignments financing resilience and assessing pol pot's cambodia by john ciorciari 2008 2009 shorenstein fellow august 1 2008 seaf news more commentary about shorenstein fellowships in contemporary asia support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studie